detail_description: Rockfort Temple Main Entrance ராஜகோபுரம் is a historic site with an ancient fort and temple located at the highest point of the fort. It played a significant role in the Carnatic wars, contributing to the establishment of British rule in India. The Ucchi Pillayar Temple, built in the 7th century, stands 83 meters high within the fort complex.
name: Rockfort Temple Main Entrance ராஜகோபுரம்
address: Tiruchirapalli Rock Fort, NSB Rd, near Krishna Readymade hall, Singarathope, Theradi Bazar, Devathanam, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620002, India

detail_description: Rock Fort, located in Tiruchirappalli, is a temple complex that sits atop a 273-foot-tall rock outcrop. The complex houses the renowned Uchchippillaiyaar Temple and the Thayumana Swamy Temple. This ancient site dates back to the Pallavas and Pandyas era and boasts a rich history of over 3.8 billion years.
name: Rock Fort
address: 11/3, South Street, Teppakulam, South St, Theppakulam, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620002, India

excerpt: Expansive, lavishly decorated temple complex dating back more than 1,000 years, with 7 enclosures.
detail_description: Sri Ranganatha Swamy Temple, located in Srirangam city of Trichy, Tamil Nadu, is a grand and ornate temple complex that dates back over 1,000 years. It consists of seven enclosures and is one of India's most renowned temples.
name: Sri Ranganatha Swamy Temple, Srirangam
address: Srirangam, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620006, India

detail_description: St. Joseph's Church in Ponmalai, Trichy is a significant historical site as it was built in 1792 during the British rule and is one of the oldest churches in India. The church played a role in the mass conversions to Christianity during that time. Adjacent to the famous St. Joseph's College, this nearly 500-year-old church boasts marvelous architecture and has been visited by notable figures such as Dr. Kalam and writer Sujatha.
name: St. Joseph's Church, Ponmalai
address: QPMG+886, Railway Colony, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620004, India

excerpt: Hindu temple dating back to the 9th century, featuring exterior stone carvings & scenic surrounds.
detail_description: Vayalur Arulmigu Murugan Saamy Temple in Tiruchirappalli is a Hindu temple dating back to the 9th century, featuring intricate exterior stone carvings and scenic surroundings. The city of Tiruchirappalli is known for its numerous religious sites, drawing devotees on memorable pilgrimage tours.
name: Arulmigu Vayalur Murugan Temple.
address: RJHF+H7W, Vayalur, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620021, India

detail_description: The Arulmigu Erumbeeswarar Temple, located in Thiruverumbur, Trichy, Tamil Nadu, is a Chola-era hilltop temple dedicated to Lord Shiva. This ancient Dravidian-style temple stands on a 60-foot-high hill and is known locally as Malai Kovil or the Hill Temple.
name: Arulmigu Erumbeeswarar Temple, Thiruverumbur (Paadal Petra Sthalam)
address: Malaikoil, Thiruverumbur, Tamil Nadu 620013, India

excerpt: Established in 1999, the planetarium offers shows in Tamil & English, plus an environmental gallery.
detail_description: The Anna Science Center Planetarium Office, established in 1999 by the Tamil Nadu government, is a popular destination for both children and adults. The planetarium offers shows in Tamil and English, featuring Japanese laser technology and now newly constructed LED panels with 5.1 surround sound and France 4K digital technology. The capacity has increased to accommodate up to 90 people.
name: Anna Science Center Planetarium Office
address: QP93+H7G, Trichy - Pudukkottai, Near Airport, Lourde Nagar, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620007, India

excerpt: This spacious, contemporary restaurant dishes up globally inspired meals with emphasis on BBQ meats.
detail_description: DiMoRa is a spacious and contemporary restaurant that offers a diverse range of cuisines, including Chinese, Indian, Tandoori, and Italian. The restaurant is the brainchild of three young entrepreneurs with extensive experience in the hotel industry. It caters to both vegetarians and meat lovers with its wide array of dishes. The ambiance, service, and food are highly praised by visitors. While some feel that certain dishes could be improved in terms of taste, the overall dining experience is considered enjoyable.
name: DiMoRa
address: No. B, 4th Floor Ambigai City Center, 29 & 30, Shastri Rd, Tennur, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620018, India

excerpt: Naturally protected fort on a huge outcrop with a temple & caves, accessible by 400 stone steps.
detail_description: Tiruchirapalli Rock Fort is a naturally fortified structure situated on a massive outcrop, featuring a temple and caves that can be reached by climbing 400 stone steps. The 83-meter-high Rock Fort Temple, also known as Rock Fort Ganapati Temple, stands atop an ancient 83-million-year-old hillock. From the peak point of Ucchi pillaiyar Koil, visitors can enjoy breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding areas.
name: Tiruchirapalli Rock Fort
address: N Andar St, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620002, India

detail_description: Our Lady of Lourdes Church, located in Tiruchirappalli, is a significant pilgrimage site and an iconic structure in the city. Built in the 17th century by Jesuit priests, this Neo-Gothic church features a 200-foot-tall spire and stunning stained glass panels depicting biblical stories. The church exudes a peaceful and serene atmosphere, making it an ideal place for worship.
name: Our Lady of Lourdes Church
address: RMGV+R34, College Rd, Annamalai Nagar, Teppakulam, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620002, India

excerpt: Ancient Shiva temple complex with elaborate interior columns & a sprawling outer wall.
detail_description: Arulmigu Jambukeswarar Akilandeswari Temple, also known as Thiruvanaikoil Temple, is a historic Shiva temple complex in Trichy. It is dedicated to Lord Shiva and features elaborate interior columns and a sprawling outer wall. The temple worships Meenakshi, another form of Goddess Parvati, and Lord Sundareshwarar.
name: Arulmigu Jambukeswarar Temple
address: VP33+5JC, N Car St, Srirangam, Thiruvanaikoil, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620005, India

detail_description: The Tiruchirappalli Rail Museum and Heritage Center, inaugurated in 2014, is a tribute to the Southern Indian Railway Company's history. It showcases over 400 artifacts and 200 photos from the company's early days. The museum was part of the South Indian Railways' 150th Sesquicentennial celebration and opened to the public in 2015 due to fund constraints.
name: Tiruchirappalli Rail Museum and Heritage Center
address: Bharathiar Salai, Bharathiyar Salai, Cantonment, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620001, India

detail_description: Arulmigu Thiru Uyyakondan Thirumalai UjjevaNathar swamy Temple, also known as Padal Petra Temple, is a 2000-year-old temple located on a 98 ft. tall stone hill surrounded by rock walls. The temple complex spans four acres and can be accessed via a flight of 100 steps.
name: Arulmigu Thiru Uyyakondan Thirumalai UjjevaNathar swamy Temple,Padal Petra Temple
address: RM85+4G7, 203, Vayalur Rd, Uyyakondanmalai, MM Nagar, Tiruchirappalli, Sholanganallur, Tamil Nadu 620102, India

excerpt: Stylish, contemporary restaurant serving Indian vegetarian dishes along with some Chinese fare.
detail_description: EZHAM SUVAI is a trendy and modern restaurant in Tiruchirappalli, India that offers a mix of Indian vegetarian dishes and Chinese cuisine. It has garnered positive reviews for its delectable food and stylish ambiance. The restaurant is known for its local flavors and street food, making it a must-visit dining destination in the city. With its contemporary setting and diverse menu, EZHAM SUVAI provides an enjoyable culinary experience for locals and tourists alike.
name: EZHAM SUVAI
address: 39, D-17, 11th Cross E Rd, Thillai Nagar East, Tennur, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620018, India

detail_description: St. Paul's Shopping Complex is a bustling hub for shopping enthusiasts, offering a wide variety of goods and services. Visitors can explore an array of shops selling hand looms, silk products, paints, car accessories, bakery items, electronics like TVs and audio equipment. Nalli Silks is a popular destination within the complex for those seeking dress materials such as sarees and shirts.
name: St. Paul's Shopping Complex
address: 418, Madurai Main Rd, Bharathiyar Salai, Sangillyandapuram, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620001, India

excerpt: Bordered by the Kaveri River, Srirangam is a city island known for being home to the vast Sri Ranganatha Swamy Temple, one of the largest in India with 81 shrines spanning 63 hectares. Pilgrims flock to the island for its many Hindu temples and wedding venues, ranging from casual to elaborate halls holding up to 1,000 guests. The area also has bridal boutiques and salons, as well as cafes and vegetarian restaurants.
detail_description: Srirangam, situated on a city island surrounded by the Kaveri River, is renowned for its expansive Sri Ranganatha Swamy Temple, one of India's largest temples featuring 81 shrines spread across 63 hectares. The island attracts pilgrims with its numerous Hindu temples and diverse wedding venues, accommodating gatherings from intimate to grand scales. Additionally, visitors can explore bridal boutiques and salons as well as savor the offerings of cafes and vegetarian restaurants.
name: Srirangam
address: Tamil Nadu, India

detail_description: Banana Leaf Restaurant in Trichy offers a unique dining experience with its authentic South Indian style of serving meals on banana leaves. The restaurant is known for its traditional taste and provides a delightful and healthy meal, especially for vegetarians. It's a great spot for couples to enjoy a special dinner. The restaurant also caters to non-vegetarian preferences and is popular for its large group-friendly ambiance, excellent food, and the novelty of serving meals on banana leaves.
name: Banana Leaf Restaurant
address: GROUND FLOOR, SUMANGALI RESIDENCY, TVS Toll Gate Rd, Subramaniyapuram, Sangillyandapuram, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620020, India

detail_description: Amma Mandapam is a bathing ghat located on the Kaveri River near Sri Ranganathaswamy Temple. It's a bustling spot where devotees take purifying dips, perform rituals, and pay homage to their ancestors. Many locals also use the water for washing clothes. However, there are concerns about cleanliness and water availability at the complex. Suggestions have been made to ensure perennial water supply and establish a separate complex for Punya rituals downstream.
name: Amma Mandapam
address: RMWQ+PWH, Srirangam, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620008, India

excerpt: Casual restaurant serving dishes from across India, doubling up as a banquet hall.
detail_description: Shri Sangeetas Veg is a popular restaurant that caters mainly to vegetarians, offering a wide variety of vegetarian dishes from different regions of India. The restaurant also functions as a banquet hall and is known for its excellent service and clean environment. It is particularly recommended for vegans, with must-try options including desserts and Pan Asian dishes. While the fresh juices are tasty but pricey, the menu offers an array of reasonably priced options.
name: Shri Sangeetas (Central Bus Stand, Trichy) Veg. Restaurant | Sweets | Savouries
address: 2, Voc Rd, near Central Bus Stand, Cantonment, Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu 620001, India

excerpt: Tiruchirappalli (also called Tiruchi or Trichy) is an ancient city in India's southern Tamil Nadu state. The Kaveri and Kollidam rivers flow around Srirangam Island, which is known for sacred Hindu sites Sri Ranganathaswamy Temple, with intricately carved gopurams (towering gateways), and Jambukeswarar-Akilandeswari Temple, dedicated to the god Shiva. The Rock Fort Temple complex towers over the city center.
detail_description: Tiruchirappalli, also known as Tiruchi or Trichy, is an ancient city in the southern state of Tamil Nadu, India. The city is surrounded by the Kaveri and Kollidam rivers and is home to Srirangam Island, which houses sacred Hindu sites such as the Sri Ranganathaswamy Temple and Jambukeswarar-Akilandeswari Temple. The Rock Fort Temple complex overlooks the city center.
name: Tiruchirappalli
address: Tamil Nadu, India
